<body>

<h1>Helpdesk Mock Scenario: Firefox Video Playback Issue</h1>

<div class="ticket">
<h2>Customer Report</h2>
<p class="customer">“Hi, I can log in and see the video library, but when I try to play any video on Firefox, it just stays loading forever. On Chrome it works perfectly. I cleared my cache and cookies but still no luck.”</p>
</div>

<div class="ticket">
<h2>Agent Response – Step 1: Gather Browser Info</h2>
<p class="agent">“Thanks for reporting this. Can you please tell me your Firefox version and operating system?”</p>
<p class="customer">“Firefox 110.0 on Windows 10.”</p>
</div>

<div class="ticket">
<h2>Agent Response – Step 2: Replicate Issue</h2>
<p class="agent">Steps:</p>
<pre>
1. Download Firefox 110 from Mozilla archive: https://ftp.mozilla.org/pub/firefox/releases/
2. Use a separate profile to avoid affecting main browser:
   firefox.exe -P "Firefox110Profile"
3. Open the site and try to play a video.
</pre>
</div>

<div class="ticket">
<h2>Agent Response – Step 3: Check Browser Capabilities</h2>
<p class="agent">Use DevTools Console:</p>
<pre>
const v = document.createElement("video");
["video/mp4; codecs='avc1.42E01E, mp4a.40.2'",
 "video/webm; codecs='vp8, vorbis'",
 "video/webm; codecs='vp9, opus'"]
.forEach(type => console.log(type, "=>", v.canPlayType(type)));
</pre>
<p>Likely outcome: Firefox 110 may not support the format the site delivers.</p>
</div>

<div class="ticket">
<h2>Agent Response – Step 4: Check Network/Playback</h2>
<pre>
1. Open Network tab → filter by 'media'
2. Attempt playback → look for failed requests or CORS errors
3. Console test:
   const videoTest = document.createElement("video");
   videoTest.src = "https://example.com/test.mp4";
   videoTest.play().catch(e => console.error("Playback failed:", e));
</pre>
</div>

<div class="ticket">
<h2>Ticket Workflow</h2>
<ul>
<li><span class="status">Open:</span> Customer reports video not playing in Firefox.</li>
<li><span class="status">Waiting on Customer:</span> Ask for Firefox version + OS.</li>
<li><span class="status">Pending:</span> Agent replicates issue in same version, finds unsupported video format. Escalates to dev team.</li>
<li><span class="status">Resolved:</span> Devs add compatible video format. Agent notifies customer.</li>
<li><span class="status">Closed:</span> Customer confirms playback works in Firefox 110.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="ticket">
<h2>Key Notes for Agents</h2>
<ul>
<li>Always ask for browser + version + OS first.</li>
<li>Use archived builds or separate profiles to replicate.</li>
<li>Playback issues are usually codec/format related, not network-only.</li>
<li>Keep track of ticket statuses exactly: Open → Waiting → Pending → Resolved → Closed.</li>
</ul>
</div>

</body>
